The objective is to create a machine-learning model from scratch to predict the sentiment of sentences.
The data-set is from -- Yelp dataset challenge http://www.yelp.com/dataset_challenge  

Dataset contains 1000 lines commenting on amazon cell products and its sentiment values.
0-Negative sentiment
1-Positive sentiment

The model is based on Naive Bayes and evaluated using accuracy, precision and recall values

Prerequisites: 
Install anaconda on system and launch spyder.
Setup & RUN: 
1)Download the "Naive.py" file and ".csv" file.
2)Set the pd.read_csv to the file location where "amazon_cells_labelled.txt" is downloaded.
3)Run the file.

Anomalies:
Sentences containing least frequent words are neglected for training.
